        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Based on firewood and charcoal usage in developing nations of 1300 Mio m3 (UCS 2011), generic wood fuel ash content, and a generic global rate of 21.7w% of MSW going to incineration (Pike + UNSD 2012). Very uncertain figure, as firewood using nations tend to have little MSWI, so a global average calculation might be misleading.

It is estimated that the remaining 78.3% goes to landfill (50%) and to landfarming (50%).</productionVolumeComment>
